Being tall, dense, gorilla-mode humans was the neandrathal's evolutionary niche. They did not reproduce quickly enough so it did not work out well for them. More > less

If anthros were physically superior to humans and otherwise equal, anthros would have to eat more, have longer gestation periods, longer puberty, lower twinning rates (which would mean no delicious multi-nips), etc, etc. Knowing biology these things would probably compound into something like 10X lower population capacity.

BTW anthros would probably have weaker lower body strength because digitigrade legs would be longer and daintier. Plantigrade legs have one fulcrum, digitigrade legs would have two fulcrums with a total of half the muscle. The strength from an additional fulcrum would only compound if each individual leg muscle was stronger than a human's but they wouldn't be due to weight considerations. So anthros would probably be faster (due to longer legs) but have weaker lower body strength and that shit definitely counts.
